ction to CSS with Example
CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is a stylesheet language used to describe the presentation of a document written in HTML. It allows you to style and layout web pages, making them visually appealing and responsive. Here's an introduction to CSS along with an example that extends the previous HTML example:

Basic CSS Structure:
CSS consists of rules that define how elements should be displayed on a web page. A rule typically consists of a selector and a declaration block.

css
/* CSS Comments - This is a comment */
selector {
    property: value;
    /* More properties and values */
}
Example CSS for the HTML Code:
css
Copy code
/* Reset some default browser styles */
body, h1, p, ul, li {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

/* Apply a background color to the header */
header {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 10px;
}

/* Style navigation links */
nav ul {
    list-style-type: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

nav a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: #333;
    padding: 5px 10px;
    display: inline-block;
}

nav a:hover {
    background-color: #ddd;
    color: #333;
}

/* Style the main content area */
article {
    background-color: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 10px;
}

section {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}

/* Style the sidebar */
aside {
    background-color: #eee;
    padding: 10px;
}

/* Style the footer */
footer {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 10px;
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 100%;
}
